    "statement (ii) does not hold) then there must be some Q i such that h(x) -h(y) ≈ const for all pairs x, y where y = x + 1 N e 1 and x ∈ Q i.",
    "If this is the case, this in particular implies that the image, under h, of Q i+1 is nearly a translation of the image of Q i.In the following lemma, we connect formal Lipschitz sums with biLipschitz maps h for which Lemma 5.8 can be used.",
    "Let d ∈ N and let i (f i, π i) be a regular formal Lipschitz sum.",
    "Denote by L i the Lipschitz constant of each π j i.",
    "Define the map h: [0, 1] d → ℓ 2 given byh(x) = d j=1 x j e j + ∞ i=1 d j=1 L d 2 -1 i π j i (x)e di+j for x ∈ [0, 1] d.The definition is valid."
  ]
